{"id":"304090209_Maia_and_Mandos_Tools_for_Integrity_Protection_on_Arbitrary_Files","abstract":"We present the results of our dissertation research, which focuses on practical means of protecting system data integrity. In particular, we present Maia, a language for describing integrity constraints on arbitrary file types, and Mandos, a Linux Security Module which uses verify-on-close to enforce mandatory integrity guarantees. We also provide details of a Maia-based verifier generator, demonstrate that Maia and Mandos introduce minimal delay in performing their tasks, and include a selection of sample Maia specifications.","authors":["Paul J. Bonamy"],"meta":["January 2016"],"references":["337289978_Linux_Security_Modules_General_Security_Support_for_the_Linux_Kernel","259490307_Detecting_meaning_in_RSVP_at_13_ms_per_picture","235043659_Integrity_Considerations_for_Secure_Computer_Systems","220880943_Integrating_Flexible_Support_for_Security_Policies_into_the_Linux_Operating_System","24164143_Role-Based_Access_Controls","313550915_An_Axiomatic_Basis_of_Computer_Programming","305263025_An_Efficient_Context-Free_Parsing_Algorithm","288351995_Information_Hiding_First_International_Workshop_proceedings","274074378_Extensible_Markup_Language_XML_10_Fifth_Edition","271447733_The_Definitive_ANTLR_4_Reference","266653206_Transforming_commodity_security_policies_to_enforce_Clark-Wilson_integrity","262241624_Paranoid_penguin_security_features_in_SUSE_100","242542144_A_foundation_of_fault-tolerant_computing","242499913_Yacc_-_Yet_Another_Compiler-Compiler","242481468_Computer_Security_Art_and_Science","242372066_Internet_Message_Access_Protocol-version_4rev1","239540811_The_setl_programming_language","234794713_The_Denotational_Semantics_of_Programming_Languages","234791826_Response_time_in_man-computer_conversational_transactions","234784735_Paranoid_penguin_An_introduction_to_Novell_AppArmor","232716949_Denotational_Semantics_A_Methodology_For_Language_Development","232640945